  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2020-07-01",
    "date": "2021-08-10T13:12:22Z",
    "text": "Coronavirus Service Corps Act \n\nThis bill establishes a Coronavirus Service Corps that must employ unemployed or underemployed citizens to carry out work such as\n\n health care, including contract tracing, administering COVID-19 tests, and peer mental health counseling; assisting essential services and the reopening of businesses; social services, including hunger relief, homeless services, and senior care. The hourly wage for corps employees must be the greater of (1) 150% of the minimum hourly wage in the applicable locality, or (2) $15 an hour."
  },
